  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The operating envelope was extended in Q3 2025 to include pediatric patients (body surface area < 0.6 m², cardiac output range 0.8–2.2 L/min), a subgroup not represented in the original 2023 validation campaign. The credibility team concluded that the existing validation evidence, obtained at adult flow rates of 3.0–6.0 L/min, provides sufficient coverage by extrapolation of the power-law hemolysis damage model to lower shear-stress regimes; no additional in-vitro or in-silico validation runs were commissioned for the pediatric sub-range.",
