      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI < 5% for the primary quantity of interest (volume-averaged scalar shear stress) at the nominal adult operating point.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation across three mesh levels yielded GCI = 2.1% at the 4.5 L/min, 3000 RPM adult operating point (ValidationResult morrison-vr-mesh-convergence-2023). The mesh study was conducted exclusively at adult flow conditions; no discretization error quantification was performed at pediatric flow rates (0.8–2.2 L/min). The team judged that mesh adequacy is preserved across the expanded envelope because the Reynolds number decreases monotonically with flow rate, making the adult mesh conservative. No supporting evidence for this extrapolation is linked."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
