      "rationale": "The 2023 in-vitro campaign used porcine blood at 37 ± 0.5 °C, hematocrit 33 ± 2%, matching CFD boundary conditions. Test conditions were representative of adult CPB practice. Pediatric CPB circuits may employ higher hemodilution ratios (hematocrit 25–28%); this difference was noted in the team's internal review but was not considered a material departure from the validated conditions, and no supplemental testing at pediatric hematocrit levels was performed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
