      "rationale": "All five adult operating-point predictions satisfied the ±15% tolerance band (tighter than the acceptance criterion). Quantitative agreement is documented in ValidationResult morrison-vr-adult-flowsweep-2023. No output comparison data exist for the pediatric flow range; the assessment team cited the adult agreement as sufficient evidence that the model will perform within tolerance across the extended envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) is directly linked to the clinical decision criterion and is measurable in vitro.",
      "rationale": "RH is the regulatory-accepted surrogate for pump-induced hemolysis and maps directly to the predicate comparison criterion. The quantity is computable from CFD shear-stress fields via the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law damage model and is measurable via modified index of hemolysis in vitro. Relevance holds across the adult and pediatric flow ranges because the damage model is formulated in terms of local shear stress and exposure time, which are flow-rate-independent in principle."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities cover the pump geometry, fluid, and operating conditions representative of the COU.",
      "rationale": "The 2023 validation campaign used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry and porcine blood, which is accepted as a surrogate for human blood in hemolysis testing. Operating conditions spanned 3.0–6.0 L/min, fully covering the original adult COU. Following the Q3 2025 label expansion, the COU now includes pediatric patients at 0.8–2.2 L/min. The validation activities do not include test points in this sub-range. The team argued that the physics-based damage model provides coverage by analogy, and that the prior validation campaign remains the sole evidentiary basis for the expanded COU without supplemental re-validation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; commercial solver residual convergence criteria documented.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, explicit numerical solver error quantification beyond residual monitoring is not required. Convergence to RMS residuals < 1 × 10⁻⁵ for all transport equations was enforced and logged. Factor scoped out per MRL 2 assessment plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
