      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; simulation workflow peer-reviewed internally.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment not required at MRL 2. Internal peer review of the simulation setup, boundary condition application, and post-processing scripts was completed by a senior analyst independent of the primary modeler. No formal use-error quantification was conducted."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; model form selection documented with literature justification.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis damage model was selected based on its widespread use in FDA-cited literature for centrifugal blood pump assessment. Model form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2. The team noted that the model's empirical coefficients were derived from adult blood under conditions similar to the original validation envelope; applicability to pediatric hemodiluted blood was not formally evaluated."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
